  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "In order to do this you need to create a custom widget. The widget API can be used this way:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nvar search = instantsearch(/*parameters*/);\r\n\r\nvar menuContainer = jQuery('.menu');\r\nsearch.addWidget({\r\n  render: function(opts) {\r\n    var results = opts.results;\r\n    var menuValues = results.getFacetValues('attribute');\r\n    var html = menuValues.map(facetToHTML);\r\n    menuContainer.html(html);\r\n  }\r\n});\r\n\r\nfunction facetToHTML(facet) {\r\n  return '<a href=\"#\">'+facet.name+'</a>';\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nEvery time there are new results in your search the method `render` of the widget will be called. It extracts the facet values and transform them into HTML string then add it to the DOM.",
